id: pm-bhhe
title: "Expand aggregate group-by to support priority, status, assignee, tags"
description: "The aggregate command currently only supports group-by parent|type. Attempting --group-by priority returns error: 'Aggregate group fields must be one of parent|type'. For a universal PM tool, grouping by priority, status, assignee, sprint, release, and tags would be essential."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,aggregate,extensibility,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-04-26T20:16:46.172Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-26T20:16:46.172Z"
deadline: "2026-05-03T20:16:46.172Z"
author: audit-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: "Aggregate supports grouping by priority, status, assignee, tags at minimum"
body: "Current behavior: only parent|type allowed. Expected: priority, status, assignee, tags, sprint, release should also be valid group-by fields. This limits the analytical capabilities for agents trying to triage and report on project state."
